			<section>
				<h2 id="secret-links">Secret Links</h2>
				<p>Can you keep a secret? There are two handy pages I made for my own use. I don&apos;t advertise them because they use massive HTML tables so the pages aren&apos;t responsive (i.e. they don&apos;t look good on mobile devices). But if you&apos;re brave you can find them here:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/videos.php" title="Click here to see the &quot;secret&quot; index of all videos. [Hotkey: V]">Videos Index</a></li>
					<li>
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/books.php" title="Click here to see the &quot;secret&quot; index of all books. [Hotkey: B]">Books Index</a></li></ul>
				<p>I also have some notes about YouTube hacks over here: 
					<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/youtube-hacks.php" title="Click here to read about YouTube hacks. [Hotkey: 3]">YouTube Hacks</a>.</p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="jjcode">New JJCODE</h2>
				<p>This is a facility for John. I use it to generate the five digit codes used in the short links. Usually this is an automated process, but sometimes I set it up manually.</p>
				<p>Here is a new JJCODE: 58297</p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="shortcuts">Shortcut Keys</h2>
				<p>There are some hotkeys you can use to speed your navigation. Just press the key for the page you want. I added this support for hotkeys because I use this website quite a lot while I&apos;m working on the show. It&apos;s mostly just here for my use but it would be cool if someone else found it useful too! I&apos;m not sure if it will work on all browsers, but it works on recent versions of Firefox and Chromium. The main hotkey you have to remember is &apos;?&apos; for this section of this page, then you can take it from there.</p>
